## Velocity Equations

Differentiating each constraint with respect to time gives:

1. x1_dot + y1_dot = 0  
2. őł1_dot = 0  
3. y2_dot - x2_dot = 0  
4. őł2_dot = 0  
5. x3_dot + (L/2)cos(őł3)őł3_dot - x1_dot = 0  
6. y3_dot + (L/2)sin(őł3)őł3_dot - y1_dot = 0  
7. x3_dot - (L/2)cos(őł3)őł3_dot - x2_dot = 0  
8. y3_dot - (L/2)sin(őł3)őł3_dot - y2_dot = 0  
9. őł3_dot - ŌČ = 0

Since the bar rotates at a constant angular speed,

őł3_dot = ŌČ = 2 rad/s

the velocity equations become:

1. x1_dot + y1_dot = 0  
2. őł1_dot = 0  
3. y2_dot - x2_dot = 0  
4. őł2_dot = 0  
5. x3_dot + (L/2)ŌČ cos(őł3) - x1_dot = 0  
6. y3_dot + (L/2)ŌČ sin(őł3) - y1_dot = 0  
7. x3_dot - (L/2)ŌČ cos(őł3) - x2_dot = 0  
8. y3_dot - (L/2)ŌČ sin(őł3) - y2_dot = 0  
9. őł3_dot = ŌČ
"""

